## Component Relationships

### How MITRE ATT&CK Connects to Everything

```
ANALYTIC-001 (Detection)
  â†“
Detects: User added to admin group
  â†“
Maps to ATT&CK: T1098.002 (Account Manipulation)
               T1136.001 (Create Account - Local Account)
  â†“
Used in: UC-001 (Use Case)
  â†“
Triggers: RE&CT Response
  â€¢ RA1001 (Collect evidence of account creation)
  â€¢ RA1002 (Identify if privileged account created)
  â€¢ RA1003 (Determine if intentional vs. attack)
  â€¢ RA3101 (Revoke admin if unauthorized)
  â†“
Response Documented in: 12-Playbooks-UC-001.md
  â€¢ Step-by-step playbook
  â€¢ Commands to execute
  â€¢ Decision trees
  â€¢ Success criteria

FINAL JIRA TICKET:
  â€¢ MITRE-ATT&CK: T1098.002
  â€¢ Use-Case: UC-001
  â€¢ RE&CT-Phase: RA1xxx â†’ RA3xxx â†’ RA4xxx â†’ RA5xxx â†’ RA6xxx
  â€¢ Playbook-Link: UC-001 playbook
  â€¢ Status transitions through JIRA workflow
```

### Relationship Matrix

| Component | Purpose | Location | Integration |
|-----------|---------|----------|-------------|
| **Analytics** | Detect threats | Splunk | Fire webhook to JIRA |
| **Use Cases** | Classify threats | 02-Use-Cases-Repository.md | Link to JIRA via custom field |
| **MITRE ATT&CK** | Threat framework | Custom field in JIRA | Auto-populated from use case |
| **RE&CT** | Response procedures | 03-REACT-Framework.md | Linked as JIRA checklist |
| **Playbooks** | Incident guides | 12-Playbooks-*.md | Linked in JIRA ticket description |
| **Runbooks** | Detailed procedures | Within playbooks | Step-by-step commands |
| **JIRA** | Orchestration | SOC-OPS project | Central system of record |

---

## Example: Complete UC-001 Incident Flow

### Starting Point: Raw Event Data

```
Windows Security Log 4728 Event:
  Computer: SERVER-001
  EventTime: 2025-01-15 14:32:00
  SubjectUserName: DOMAIN\admin-user
  TargetUserName: DOMAIN\new-user
  TargetGroupName: Domain Admins
  EventID: 4728
```

### Step 1: Detection (Analytics Layer)

**ANALYTIC-001 Query in Splunk:**
```spl
index=windows EventCode=4728 
| stats count by SubjectUserName, TargetUserName, Computer
| where count >= 1
```

**Alert Fires:**
- Alert name: "UC-001-AdminGroupAdd"
- Severity: "High"
- Host: "SERVER-001"
- User: "DOMAIN\new-user"
- Actor: "DOMAIN\admin-user"

### Step 2: Orchestration (JIRA Creation)

**Webhook Sent to JIRA:**
```json
{
  "alert_name": "UC-001-AdminGroupAdd",
  "severity": "High",
  "analytic_id": "ANALYTIC-001",
  "host": "SERVER-001",
  "user": "DOMAIN\\new-user",
  "actor": "DOMAIN\\admin-user",
  "timestamp": "2025-01-15T14:32:00Z"
}
```

**JIRA Automation Rules Execute:**

1. **Rule 1:** Create ticket
   ```
   Title: "[High] UC-001 - Admin Added to Group - SERVER-001"
   Description: (Auto-populated with alert details)
   Status: Triage
   ```

2. **Rule 2:** Enrich with use case
   ```
   Custom Fields Set:
   â€¢ Use-Case: UC-001
   â€¢ MITRE-ATT&CK: T1098.002
   â€¢ RE&CT-Phase: RA1xxx
   â€¢ Playbook-Link: 12-Playbooks-UC-001.md
   
   Comment Added:
   "Investigation runbook: UC-001 - Local Administrator Group Modification
    Contact actor and manager to verify legitimacy.
    See playbook for full procedure."
   ```

3. **Rule 3:** Set SLA and assign
   ```
   Custom Fields:
   â€¢ SLA-Response: 15 minutes
   â€¢ SLA-Resolution: 8 hours
   â€¢ Assigned-To: On-call-analyst-john
   
   Slack Notification:
   "ðŸš¨ [HIGH] Investigation assigned to @john
    UC-001: Admin Group Addition on SERVER-001
    Runbook: [link]"
   ```

### Step 3: Investigation (Analyst Uses Playbook)

**Analyst opens: 12-Playbooks-UC-001.md**

**Triage Phase (5 min):**
```
1. Validate alert in Splunk âœ“
2. Check current group membership:
   > Get-ADGroupMember "Domain Admins"
   Result: new-user IS still in group
3. Quick assessment: Actor is known IT admin, timing is business hours
   Conclusion: Possible legitimate, needs investigation
```

**Investigation Phase (10 min):**
```
1. Contact actor (admin-user):
   "I need to verify a permission change at 14:32 today.
    You added new-user to Domain Admins.
    Can you explain the business reason?"
   
   Response: "Yes, we provisioned new-user as system admin
              per change request CH-12345. Manager approved."

2. Verify change ticket:
   Query system: CH-12345
   Status: APPROVED by Department Manager
   Approval date: 2025-01-14
   Implementation date: 2025-01-15 (today)
   Matches action âœ“

3. Verdict: TRUE POSITIVE (but legitimate)
   Conclusion: This was authorized privilege change
```

**Update JIRA:**
```
Status: Investigation â†’ Closed
Verdict: TRUE POSITIVE (Authorized)
Comment: "Verified with actor and change control.
          CH-12345 approved by manager.
          Action is legitimate."
```

### Step 4: Closure and Metrics

**JIRA Auto-Calculation:**
```
Metrics:
â€¢ MTTT (Mean Time to Triage): 3 minutes
â€¢ MTTD (Mean Time to Detect): 2 minutes (Splunk to alert)
â€¢ MTTC (Mean Time to Contain): N/A (no containment needed)
â€¢ MTTR (Mean Time to Resolve): 13 minutes
â€¢ SLA Response: 15 min target, 3 min actual âœ“
â€¢ SLA Resolution: 8 hour target, 13 min actual âœ“
```

**Lessons Learned (RA6xxx):**
```
Detection Effectiveness: âœ“
  â€¢ Detection fired quickly
  â€¢ Playbook guided investigation
  â€¢ Clear decision made rapidly

Improvement Opportunity:
  â€¢ Could pre-check change tickets to reduce false positives
  â€¢ Filter: Alert + valid change ticket = auto-close in future

Implementation:
  â€¢ Update ANALYTIC-001 tuning
  â€¢ Add pre-check for change tickets in JIRA automation
```

