## True Positive vs False Positive Example

### Scenario A: Same Alert, Different Context (FALSE POSITIVE)

```
SAME ALERT FIRES:
Event: new-user2 added to Domain Admins
Time: 2025-01-15 22:45:00 (off-hours)

TRIAGE:
â€¢ Off-hours suspicious âš 
â€¢ Different admin actor âš 
â€¢ No change ticket found âš 

INVESTIGATION:
1. Contact admin-user2:
   "I need to verify a permission change at 22:45 today."
   Response: "I didn't do anything like that. I was home."
   
2. Check for compromised admin account:
   Look for other suspicious activity:
   â€¢ Multiple other groups modified?
   â€¢ Unusual logons?
   â€¢ Lateral movement?
   
3. Verification shows: admin-user2 account likely compromised

VERDICT: TRUE POSITIVE (Attack)

RE&CT EXECUTION:
â†’ Move to Containment (RA3xxx)
  â€¢ Reset admin-user2 password
  â€¢ Revoke new-user2 from admin group
  â€¢ Scan for lateral movement
  â€¢ Reset all admin passwords
```

### Scenario B: Same Alert, Different Context (TRUE POSITIVE)

```
SAME ALERT FIRES:
Event: new-user3 added to Domain Admins
Time: 2025-01-15 09:00:00 (business hours)

TRIAGE:
â€¢ Business hours âœ“
â€¢ Known IT admin actor âœ“
â€¢ Manager is known to request provisioning âœ“

INVESTIGATION:
1. Contact admin-user:
   "I provisioned new-user3 today as per CH-12346.
    They're our new infrastructure engineer."
   
2. Verify CH-12346:
   Pre-approved admin onboarding request
   Approval: Director of Infrastructure
   Implementation: Same day as alert

VERDICT: FALSE POSITIVE (Legitimate)

JIRA CLOSURE:
â†’ Move to Closed
â†’ Document as authorized change
â†’ Update whitelist for future reference
```

